// // This module calculates the absolute value of a 4-bit signed input. When the input 'a' is positive, the output 'y' will be the negation of 'a'. If 'a' is non-positive, 'y' will simply be equal to 'a'.
module top_module(input signed [3:0] a, output [3:0] y);assign y = a[3] ? -a : a;
